d","fees":{},"offering_terms":"","fees_table":"","erg":[],"campus":{"name":""}},"additional_information":"","study_level_tooltip":"Undergraduate: A level of study that leads to the award of a Diploma, Advanced Diploma, Associate Degree or a Bachelor Degree (pass or honours).","campus":"Paddington","study_level_single":{"label":"Undergraduate","value":"ugrd"},"code":"SDES2408","attributes":[],"credit_points_header":"6 Units of Credit","eqivalents":[],"exclusion":[],"search_title":"SDES2408 - Jewellery Narratives, Concepts and Materials","description":"<p>Jewellery Narratives, Concepts and Materials introduces students to the language of Jewellery and Object design through conceptual exploration, the acquisition of technical knowledge and studio based material investigations. Projects will employ a series of personal narratives and stories to explore and address stages of the design process, and implement critical analysis, research, problem-solving and design development culminating in the fabrication of finished jewellery design solutions. Communication techniques utilising two-dimensional and three-dimensional formats and basic computer skills will be developed.</p><br /><p>Students will be presented with a series of lectures and demonstrations informing them of the different skills, knowledge and abilities required in order to undertake the creation of a three dimensional object.This course will develop students understanding of studio based jewellery practice through investigations of materials and jewellery processes. In practical terms students will examine the technology of metal and its translation through heat into three-dimensional forms.The techniques of soldering, casting and fabrication will be explored using non-ferrous metals, to translate design drawings and models into three-dimensional jewellery objects both wearable and non-wearable.</p><br /><p>Assessment in this course is based on submission and evaluation of a three stage project development process including:</p><br /><ol><li>Material investigations and conceptual studies</li><li>Design proposal and statement examining possible solutions</li><li>Narrative outcome evidenced in the final object presentation and documentation </li></ol><br /><p>SDES2408 Jewellery Narratives, Concepts and Materialsis is an introductory 2000 level studio course. It is one of a suite of  two (or more) interrelated core courses in Year 2 that contribute to a four-course specialist &#39;stream&#39; in the BFA(Hons), BMA(Hons) and/or BDes(Hons) programs completed over Years 2 and 3.</p><br /><p>This course relates to companion courses in the Jewellery studio stream particularly SDES2409 by providing an introduction to contemporary jewellery and object design in association with other  Year 2 courses in preparation for more advanced studies in Year 3.</p>","hb_assessments":[{"delivery_variation":{"cl_id":"3ede70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a96199f","name":"Blended in-person / online - Standard (usually weekly or fortnightly)"},"assessments":[{"individual":{"label":null,"value":null},"assessment_name":"The Significant Object","assessment_type":{"label":"Lab work","value":"lab_work"},"assessment_id":"1","weighting":"50","description":"The personal Narratives developed by the students in the Proposal of Task 2 are to be refined and built to finished wearable objects in the jewellery studio for this Task 3. Techniques and processes learnt in task 1 are to be extended. The jewellery objects  are to be supported by a postcard and concept statement that contextualises the design outcomes.<br />Students will receive both written and verbal feedback","learning_outcomes":[{"value":"CLO4","cl_id":"32de70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a96199c","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO1","cl_id":"6ade70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a961993","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO2","cl_id":"b6de70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a961996","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO3","cl_id":"f2de70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a961999","key":"code"}],"delivery_variations":[],"applies_to_all_delivery_variations":"true","cl_id":"12de70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a961981","links":[]},{"individual":{"label":null,"value":null},"assessment_name":"Narrative approaches to material investigations and conceptual studies","assessment_type":{"label":"Lab work","value":"lab_work"},"assessment_id":"2","weighting":"40","description":"Students are required to apply conceptual frameworks for ideas generation and create a family of objects using metal fabrication techniques and lost wax casting processes.

Objective: 3 copper ring designs that investigate the actions of subtraction, supplementation and transformation.
This technical and conceptual project involves experimentation across a series of rings exploring possible variations initially applied to an identical unit.<br />Students will receive both written and verbal feedback as part of the assessment process.","learning_outcomes":[{"value":"CLO1","cl_id":"6ade70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a961993","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO2","cl_id":"b6de70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a961996","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO3","cl_id":"f2de70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a961999","key":"code"}],"delivery_variations":[],"applies_to_all_delivery_variations":"true","cl_id":"6ade70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a961985","links":[]},{"individual":{"label":null,"value":null},"assessment_name":"Research and Concepts Proposal","assessment_type":{"label":"Essay","value":"essay"},"assessment_id":"3","weighting":"10","description":"Students will present a research report (max 1000 words) that culminates in a design proposal for a wearable work. The proposal should respond to background research such as the jewellery of individual artists, concepts of interest in contemporary jewellery practice, cultural contexts and material applications  and articulate how the student has applied this research to a  conceptual framework.Visual findings and conceptual ideas for your jewellery design are to be presented as a document that included drawings  for the design and construction of a significant object or series of objects.<br />Students will receive both written and verbal feedback","learning_outcomes":[{"value":"CLO4","cl_id":"32de70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a96199c","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO1","cl_id":"6ade70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a961993","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO2","cl_id":"b6de70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a961996","key":"code"}],"delivery_variations":[],"applies_to_all_delivery_variations":"true","cl_id":"a2de70bfdbf51c50eb6b147a3a96198a","links":[]}]}],"inactive_course_alert":null,"timetableURL":"http://timetable.unsw.edu.au/2021/SDES2408.html","subject_sample_text_staticcontent":"To access course outline, please visit:","links":[]}
